column5: Here are a few pic's from last week.
Nice fish! and congrats on the moose!!! Good eats for the winter months
congrats on the moose, perfect bull  we missed a cow, no shot on the bull and saw a caribou.
How hard was it to drag that thing out of the lake and onto the beach?  I kid I kid!   LOL!!!
didja hafta get another freezer just for Bullwinkle ? Nice day of surf and turf, hope you don't dull too many blades processing him
nice pictures...   My brothers group got an 800lb bull...  And a whack of walleye too...  Up around red lake...  Crazy far drive from Cornwall...lol
Nice bull...and REALLY nice walleye, wow!!!
The Red Lake just north of Ear Falls???  Crazy amounts of moose up that way

Nice job!  Sounds like a great way to spend a week!  I think next year, I'm going to send my wife to the caribean for a week with her friends, and then take off moose hunting with the boys..  Never been before, looks like a blast.
Nice! You're gonna be eatin right for a while!
awesome post
I wish I could have some moose burgers/steaks too. Nice catches!
Nice !!! Looks like a perfect kill shot too
yup  About 75km north west...  Over 2,000 km from home!!!
congrats !!! nice trip for sure...cheers
I used to live/work up there. It's tough to even get to the speed limit on that highway before your slowing down for a moose, lol
Nice Moose Congrats!!!!
What kind of sausages are you gonna get done up???
This guy won't be too bad just a young bull, maybe some pepperettes but mostly ground burger,steaks and roasts.
Nice.  I got fat back

Jeez, now I'm really thinking about doing my PAL/Hunter's safety course now. I'm hoping to go for Moose or Elk next year if I can get the courses out of the way and get halfway comfortable with my rifle again (I haven't done any real shooting in over 10 years, I used to shoot sub MOA at 200 yds with my .300WinMag). Nice Moose, pike and walleye. Isn't the far north nice???
